---
title: Grilled Turkish-Inspired Double Pork Chops with Grilled Veggie Tabbouleh and Lemon-Feta Sauce
description: Pork chops just taste better grilled! Fragrant Turkish-style spice blend, pork and a colourful grilled veggie tabbouleh complement each other perfectly. Topped with a creamy, lemony feta sauce, this dish is summer at its best!

Ingredients: Pork chop • Zucchini • Sweet bell pepper • Red onion • Bulgur wheat (durum wheat semolina) (wheat) • Lemon • Mayonnaise (canola and/or soy oil, liquid whole egg, frozen egg yolk, water, salt, sugar, vinegar, concentrated lemon juice, spice extract, mustard, lactic acid, calcium disodium EDTA) (mustard, egg) • Mixed olives (pitted green olives, pitted kalamata olives, water, salt, lactic acid, potassium sorbate, vinegar, calcium chloride) • Feta cheese (pasteurized milk, partly skimmed milk, water, salt, lipase, bacterial culture, microbial enzyme, cellulose, natamycin, calcium chloride) (milk) • Chicken broth concentrate (sugars (maltodextrin, sugar), chicken stock, chicken fat, chicken flavor (chicken broth, salt, flavoring, water, glutamic acid, chicken fat, chicken powder, xanthan gum, organic sunflower oil), salt, yeast extract, xanthan gum, natural flavor) • Turkish spice blend (paprika powder, spices, onion powder, garlic powder, salt, herbs, oleoresin paprika, canola oil, silicon dioxide) (sulphites) • Parsley.
